#!/usr/bib/env python
from __future__ import print_function
from builtins import str
import argparse
import textwrap
from builtins import input
from titletobib.crossref import get_bib_from_title


def save_output_bibs(bibs, output_file):
    with open(output_file, 'w') as bibfile:
        for bib in bibs:
            bibfile.write("{}\n".format(bib))


def main():
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
        prog="titletobib",
        formatter_class=argparse.RawDescriptionHelpFormatter,
        description=textwrap.dedent('''\
        Convert a list of titles in a bibfile.
        -----------------------------------------------------
            @author: Bruno Messias
            @email: messias.physics@gmail.com
            @telegram: @bruno_messias
            @github: https://github.com/devmessias/titletobib
        ''')
    )

    parser.add_argument(
        "--input", "-i",
        type=argparse.FileType("r"),
        help="input file"
    )
    parser.add_argument(
        "--output", "-o",
        help="bibtex output file")

    args = parser.parse_known_args()
    inlineTitle = len(args[1]) > 0
    if inlineTitle:
        titles = [" ".join(args[1])]
    else:
        titles = args[0].input.read()
        titles = [title for title in titles.split("\n") if title != ""]
    bibs = []
    if inlineTitle:
        get_first = False
    else:
        get_first = True if input("Automatic mode?y(yes)|n(no)") == "y" else False
    for title in titles:
        found, bib = get_bib_from_title(title, get_first)
        if found:
            bibs.append(bib)

    if len(bibs) > 0:
        if inlineTitle:
            print("\n\n")
            print(bibs[0])
        else:
            save_output_bibs(bibs, args[0].output)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
